  "original_title": "\u0d9c\u0db8\u0dca\u0db6\u0daf \u0daf\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0db1\u0dca\u0da7 \u0db6\u0dc3\u0dca \u0db1\u0dd0\u0dad\u0dd2\u0dc0\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0dc4\u0ddc\u0dad\u0dca \u2018\u0dc3\u0dd2\u0db4\u0dd9\u0da7\u0dca\u0d9a\u0ddd\u2019 \u0dc0\u0d9c\u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dc0 \u0dba\u0dd4\u0dad\u0dd4\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "If rural children miss buses, 'Sipetco' should be held responsible",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Mr. Gemunu Wijeratne, President of the Private Bus Owners' Association, said today (14) in the morning that filling stations should be provided for buses to get fuel in the rural areas that are not near the Langama depot and if the children are inconvenienced by the non-running of the buses in the rural areas, the 'Sipetco' should take responsibility.",
        "Since there are no Langama depots near Hakmana, Deniya, Dikwella, Middeniya, Beliaatta, Hambantota, Suriyawewa and Tissamaharama in the southern province, several petrol stations have been named by KR. Mr. Gemunu Wijeratne said that although he requested to increase the fuel limit in the code, Cipetco failed to do so, as there is no Hakmana depot, he has to travel 27 km to go to Depole and 40 km to get diesel for buses in Maoya area of \u200b\u200bAmpara district.",
        "Mr. Gemunu Wijeratne said that 90 percent of the private buses or 12,000 buses are expected to run tomorrow and then between 15,000 and 16,000 buses."
      ],
